data-triple-N3.o: "Galicia is an autonomous community in northwest Spain, with the official status of a nationality. It comprises the provinces of A Coruna, Lugo, Ourense and Pontevedra, being bordered by Portugal to the south, the Spanish autonomous communities of Castile and Leon and Asturias to the east, the Atlantic Ocean to the west, and the Bay of Biscay to the north. It had a population of 2,778,913 in 2012, and has a total area of 29,574km ."@en
